---
// Triptych altarpiece, painterly repaint with enriched detail.
// Each panel is an abstract, surreal SVG painting, a loose three-part homage to
// Bosch, not a copy. Painting techniques: radial gradients with off-centre light,
// blurred atmosphere haze (feGaussianBlur), radial glow fields, an feTurbulence
// grain overlay for canvas tooth, organic hand-drawn paths and layered
// translucent shapes. Forms are built from several overlapping passes (base fill,
// shade gradient for volume, spark gradient for the light catch) so there is
// light-to-shadow modelling. Only two filters per panel (soft blur, grain), the
// rest is cheap gradient fills, so the page stays light. No animation.
//
// Captions sit in a protected band: the art stops above y 250 and each caption
// has padding and a soft radial backing in the ground colour so no stroke
// crosses the glyphs. The caption is outside .panel__scene, so it stays full
// colour and legible in the grisaille closed state.
//
// Palette is keyed to the two site themes via the same data-theme mechanism
// Layout uses. The flip (black) theme is the primary look: bright forms on a
// near-black field, gilded gold frame, warm glows. The default (yellow) theme
// inverts to dark forms and deep gold on a warm amber field.
//
// Structure, open-on-load grisaille, hover and tap expand, carousel and
// reduced-motion handling are unchanged.
